title: Short Poetry Collection 118
description: This is a collection of 30 poems read by LibriVox volunteers for March 2013. This project contains the following: After Love by Sara Teasdale (1884-1933) Casey's Revenge by James Wilson (1880-1954) City Trees by Edna St. Vincent Millay (1892-1950) Closing Rhymes by William Butler Yeats (1865-1939) Darkness by Lord Byron (1788-1824) Epilogue by Charles Baudelaire (1821-1867) Translated by Arthur Symons (1865-1945) Ford O’ Kabul River by Rudyard Kipling (1865-1936) Going for Water by Robert Frost (1874-1963) If I Should Die by Ben King (1857–1894) In a Station of the Metro by Ezra Pound (1885-1972) Law by James Beattie (1735-1803) The Love Song of J. Alfred Prufrock by T. S. Eliot (1888–1965) Mending Wall by Robert Frost (1874-1963) My Shadow by Robert Louis Stevenson (1850-1894) My Summer Retreat by George R Sims (1847-1922) Never Give all the Heart by William Butler Yeats (1865–1939) New Year by Ella Wheeler Wilcox (1850-1919) Non Sum Qualis Eram Bonae sub Regno Cynarae by Ernest Dowson (1867-1900) A Pact by Ezra Pound (1885-1972) The Pessimist by Ben King (1857–1894) Rondeau by Leigh Hunt (1784-1859) Silence by Edgar Lee Masters (1868-1950) Sonnet 18 by William Shakespeare (1564-1616) The Stars Stand Up in the Air by Thomas MacDonagh (1878-1916) Suicide in the Trenches by Siegfried Sassoon (1886-1967) The Telephone by Robert Frost (1874-1963) The Two Old Bachelors by Edward Lear (1812-1888) The Voyage to Vinland by James Russell Lowell (1819-1891) Was, Is, and Yet-To-Be by Ella Wheeler Wilcox (1850-1919) When I Was Young by James Stephens (1882-1950) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
